%description:
TCP AccECN (Workstream G) G3.1: 3WHS negotiation, client AccECN-capable
(tcpEcnMode="accecn") but the server has ECN off entirely
(tcpEcnMode="off", the default). The server's SEWA-carrying SYN doesn't
match either the AccECN check (server's ecnMode isn't accecn/accecn-passive)
or the classic check (AE=1 blocks it, same as the classic-fallback
scenario), and the server's own ecnWillingness is false too, so it replies
with a completely plain SYN-ACK (no ECE, no CWR, no AE). The client's G3.1
decode logic doesn't match either recognized codepoint and falls to "no ECN
at all" (ect stays false, accEcnNegotiated stays false).

Real two-INET-instance handshake (see tcp_accecn_negotiate_accepted_1.test
for why this isn't hand-injected).

%inifile: omnetpp.ini
[General]
record-vector-results = false
ned-path = .;../../../../src;../../lib

network = inet.test.moduletest.lib.TcpTestNet1

cmdenv-event-banners=false
cmdenv-express-mode=false
cmdenv-log-prefix="[%c]: "

*.testing=false
*.tcptester.script=""

*.cli_app.localAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.cli_app.localPort=1000
*.cli_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.cli_app.connectPort=2000
*.cli_app.active=true
*.cli_app.tOpen=0s
*.cli_app.tSend=-1s
*.cli_app.sendBytes=0B
*.cli_app.tClose=-1s
*.cli_app.sendScript=""

*.srv_app.localAddress="10.0.0.2"
*.srv_app.localPort=2000
*.srv_app.connectAddress="10.0.0.1"
*.srv_app.connectPort=1000
*.srv_app.active=false
*.srv_app.tOpen=0s
*.srv_app.tSend=-1s
*.srv_app.sendBytes=0B
*.srv_app.tClose=-1s
*.srv_app.sendScript=""

*.*_tcp.sackSupport = false
*.*_tcp.windowScalingSupport = false
*.*_tcp.timestampSupport = false
*.*_tcp.mss = 1000
*.*_tcp.tcpAlgorithmClass = "TcpReno"

*.cli_tcp.tcpEcnMode = "accecn"
*.srv_tcp.tcpEcnMode = "off"

include ../../lib/tcp-legacy.ini

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: postrun.pl
open FILE, '<test.out';
while($sor = <FILE>)
{
    if ($sor =~ /^\[testing\]: (.*)$/)
    {
        print "$1\n";
    }
}
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command:  perl ./postrun.pl
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Client's SYN: SEWA, as always.
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.001 A001] A.1000 > B.2000: S E W N 0:0(0) win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# Server's SYN-ACK: plain S. -- no ECN bits at all.
%contains: postrun-command(1).out
[0.003 B001] A.1000 < B.2000: A S 500:500(0) ack 1 win 7504   Option(s): MaxSegSize
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%contains: stdout
AccECN request received a non-ECN-setup SYN-ACK... ECN is disabled.
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
